5.title: Mod Cabin

episode of.title: Fixer Upper: Behind the Design (TV Series 2018– )

5.plot: Chip and Joanna help their friend turn a small house on his land into a youthful bachelor retreat for his son. Jo gives the home a modern mountain cabin feel with black metal and warm wood accents and a beautiful rock fire pit.

6.title: A Classic

episode of.title: Fixer Upper: Behind the Design (TV Series 2018– )

6.plot: Joanna teams up with the Lee family to turn their plain-Jane house into a classic beauty. The Lees' mutual love for a clean, traditional style presents a challenge for Jo, who must find a way to fill the home with character.

7.title: Big Budget

episode of.title: Fixer Upper: Behind the Design (TV Series 2018– )

7.plot: Jo helps a family turn their outdated ranch home into a French country retreat. She uses soft neutral colors, natural wood tones and floor-to-ceiling windows to blend the existing traditional elements with the new.

8.title: Upgrade

episode of.title: Fixer Upper: Behind the Design (TV Series 2018– )

8.plot: Joanna Gaines and her design team bring traditional charm and character to a 1980s-era home in Woodway. During the reveal, Chip and Jo surprise the family with a beautiful master bathroom that wasn't seen on the original episode.

9.title: Flip House

episode of.title: Fixer Upper: Behind the Design (TV Series 2018– )

9.plot: Joanna designs a house for her sister, brother-in-law and their five children. Jo cohesively blends vintage, modern and retro styles before designing three unique rooms for the kids not featured in the original episode.

10.title: Hello Waco

episode of.title: Fixer Upper: Behind the Design (TV Series 2018– )

10.plot: Jo blends the clean and simple look of Scandinavian design with the textures and patterns of Moroccan style in an 1890s farmhouse. She also adds a beautiful second bathroom and a cozy attic bedroom.

11.title: Reimagined

episode of.title: Fixer Upper: Behind the Design (TV Series 2018– )

11.plot: Joanna Gaines and her design team convert a 1970s ranch house into a modern Mediterranean retreat. She also reveals a surprise room that was not featured in the original Fixer Upper episode.

12.title: Old World

episode of.title: Fixer Upper: Behind the Design (TV Series 2018– )

12.plot: Joanna Gaines makes a newly constructed home feel like a cozy, European cottage. From antique doors and mantles to warm woods and soft paint colors, Jo goes all out to infuse some Old-World charm into this brand new house.

13.title: Rock Star

episode of.title: Fixer Upper: Behind the Design (TV Series 2018– )

13.plot: Joanna restores a 100-year-old home for the Herrera family. In addition to preserving the charm of the original house, she creates a modern farmhouse-style design and implements a library wall and the number nine into the decor.

1.title: The Baker House

episode of.title: Fixer Upper: Behind the Design (TV Series 2018– )

1.plot: Joanna turns a little bungalow into a cozy cottage retreat for a woman after the passing of her husband. She and Chip create a dream home with light neutral colors, natural wood elements and spaces to hang photos and memorabilia.

3.title: The Scrivano House

episode of.title: Fixer Upper: Behind the Design (TV Series 2018– )

3.plot: Joanna Gaines and her team incorporate a couple's traditional and modern styles into a Tudor-style home while preserving its historic charm. Plus, Jo reveals a wallpaper-covered guest bathroom not featured in the original episode.

4.title: The Ivy House

episode of.title: Fixer Upper: Behind the Design (TV Series 2018– )

4.plot: Joanna Gaines and her design team transform the outdated Ivy House into a one-of-a-kind forever home for the Jackson family; the homeowners have not one but two design styles they'd like incorporated in the house: rustic and coastal.

akas: Fixer Upper: Behind the Design (United States)
plot: Joanna Gaines gives the full story behind bringing details and designs together for her season 5 Fixer Upper clients. She unveils surprises viewers didn't see in the original episodes, and gives a peek at never-before-seen rooms.
